Dorsal idiosoma ( Fig. 5 ). Idiosoma 900 (870–950) long and 600 (570–650) wide at widest level. Dorsal shield reticulate (except in central region of podonotal region, smooth) and punctate; 815 (735–830) long and 520 (483– 542) wide at level of coxa III, attenuate posteriorly; with 28 pairs of setae ( j 1– j 6, z 1, z 2, z 5, z 6, s 2– s 6, r 2– r 4, J 2, J 5, Z 1, Z 3– Z 5, S 1, S 2, S 4 and S 5) and 22 pairs of distinguishable pores; with a cell-like depression ( cj 3) between j 2 and j 3; with procurved line well developed posteriad of j 6, z 6, s 5 and r 4; with a posterior depression encompassing pore pZ5 and insertions of J5 and Z 5. Unsclerotised cuticle laterad of dorsal shield with nine pairs of setae ( r 5, r 6, R 1–6 and R x). Measurements of setae: j 1 44 (41–48); j 2 57 (50–65); j 3 63 (58–64); j 4 65 (60–70); j 5 67 (63–70); j 6 43 (38–48); z 1 19 (14–25); z 2 65 (57–70); z 5 42 (39–45); z 6 51 (45–55);
